article.headline: N. Arizona 113, Northern New Mexico 68
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- Cameron Jones scored 28 points and Northern Arizona had six players score in double digits in a 113-68 win over NAIA Northern New Mexico on Wednesday night. Jones scored 21 of his 28 in the first half for the Lumberjacks (6-7), who put up 62 points in the opening frame, just one shy of a school record set during the 1984-85 season against Adams State. Leading 36-20, Northern Arizona then went on a 20-5 run to put the game even further out of reach. DeAngelo Jones and Gabe Rogers each added 14 points in the victory and Shane Johannsen chipped in with 12. Senior Nick Larson notched his first career double-double with 11 points and 11 rebounds. Luis Flores also had 11 points for the Lumberjacks. Eddie Fields led Northern New Mexico (2-9) with 23 points and Billy Grayson added 20.
